description:
In rust/lichen-coap/src/codec.rs:456-462, the content_format() method was refactored to use byte array slicing:

    let bytes = format.to_be_bytes();
    let value = match format {
        0 => &bytes[2..2],      // BUG: bytes is [u8; 2], not [u8; 3]
        1..=0xFF => &bytes[1..2],
        _ => &bytes[0..2],
    };

format.to_be_bytes() returns [u8; 2], not [u8; 3]. The slice &bytes[2..2] is always empty (which is correct for format=0), and &bytes[1..2] is the low byte (correct), but the indices are confusing.

Location: rust/lichen-coap/src/codec.rs:456-462
Risk: Code is correct but misleading; future maintainers may misread the intent.
Fix: Either use explicit indexing (&[bytes[1]]) or add a comment clarifying the slice semantics.
